weakness.desc:
Ensuring that coding policies include logging capabilities at the planning and design stages is a challenge due to the lack of presence of security concerns in the design phase and tooling.&nbsp; In addition, there are many logging features which may be implemented in microservices and an absence of clear policies can result in lack of ownership from key parties, including developers.&nbsp;&nbsp;<div>
  Usually application logging is added after the fact as a response to an incident or audit.&nbsp; Ensuring that application logs, starting with authentication logs, are captured for existing applications is a challenge due to lack of resources to modify the application and necessary guidance to do so.&nbsp;&nbsp;This will result in diminishing incident response and detection capabilities.&nbsp; 
</div>

Ensuring that coding policies include logging capabilities at the planning and design stages is a challenge due to the lack of presence of security concerns in the design phase and tooling.&nbsp; In addition, there are many logging features which may be implemented in microservices and an absence of clear policies can result in lack of ownership from key parties, including developers.&nbsp;&nbsp;<div>
  Usually application logging is added after the fact as a response to an incident or audit.&nbsp; Ensuring that application logs, starting with authentication logs, are captured for existing applications is a challenge due to lack of resources to modify the application and necessary guidance to do so.&nbsp;&nbsp;This will result in diminishing incident response and detection capabilities.&nbsp; 
</div>

When using a second factor authentication, an attacker who gains access to this second factor
                        and could guess the first one could gain persistent access to the system if there are no
                        mechanisms in place to avoid this.&nbsp;
